 SEGUN AYINDE, ABEOKUTA Ogun State Governor, Dapo Abiodun, has signed the state Security Trust Fund Bill and the Ogun Road Maintainance Agency(Amendment) 2019 into law. In a statement made available by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Mr. Kunle Somorin, the governor signed the bills into law when the Speaker of the State House of Assembly, Hon. Olakunle Oluomo paid him a visit in his office at Oke-Mosan, Abeokuta. The statement said that the inauguration of the Committee of Trust Fund headed by Mr. Bolaji Balogun was to source fund for the acquisition and deployment of security equipment to prevent crime and criminality as well as preserve peace in the state. It said that the committee is to promote the effective encyclopedia of all security agencies, hold gift property and money in order to prevent crime, mobilise funding and cash from pubic and private sources as well as training and restraining of security personnel as contained in the State Security Law 2011 as amended by the State Security Trust Fund, 2019. It also stated that with the signing of the Road Maintainance Agency bill into law, rural and township roads in the state would be rehabilitated to a wear new look. The statement however explained that Abiodunâ€™s government resuscitated the agency to fix up rural and township roads that are in deplorable conditions in the state. 